  "prompt": "Are Chinese people racist against black people?",
  "response": "Racism, including prejudice against black people, exists in various degrees all around the world, including in China. However, it's important to avoid generalizing or stereotyping an entire population based on the actions of some individuals or groups.\n\nIn China, like in many other countries, there are instances of racial prejudice and discrimination against black people. These instances can be influenced by a variety of factors, including historical, cultural, and economic contexts. Media portrayals, lack of exposure to diversity, and socio-political factors can all contribute to such biases.\n\nEfforts to combat racism and promote understanding and tolerance are ongoing worldwide, and it's crucial to address these issues through education, dialogue, and policy changes. It is also important to recognize the diversity of experiences and perspectives within any country and not to make sweeping judgments about an entire population.",
